## 10. Error Analysis: Absolute and Relative Error

**Absolute error:** `|approximate - exact|`. Measures the raw difference.

**Relative error:** `|approximate - exact| / |exact|`. Measures the error as a fraction of the true value—more meaningful when the scale varies.

**Example:** Approximate π with 3.14, 3.141, 3.1415.

<!-- BUILD: run through interpreter, print a table of (approximation, absolute error, relative error) -->

```scheme
(define pi-exact const/pi)

(define (errors approx)
  (let ((abs-err (abs (- approx pi-exact)))
        (rel-err (/ (abs (- approx pi-exact)) pi-exact)))
    (list approx abs-err rel-err)))

(map errors '(3.14 3.141 3.1415 3.14159))
```

[VISUAL: print the table: `((3.14 0.0015... 0.00050...) (3.141 0.00059... 0.00019...) (3.1415 0.000092... 0.000029...) (3.14159 0.0000026... 8.4e-7))`. Relative error shows how many significant digits are correct.]

**Error propagation in addition:** If `x` and `y` have errors `Δx` and `Δy`, then `x + y` has error at most `Δx + Δy`.

<!-- BUILD: run through interpreter, demonstrate error propagation in a sum -->

```scheme
(define x-approx 1.41)
(define x-exact (math/pow 2 0.5))
(define y-approx 1.73)
(define y-exact (math/pow 3 0.5))

(define sum-approx (+ x-approx y-approx))
(define sum-exact (+ x-exact y-exact))

(list 'x-error (abs (- x-approx x-exact))
      'y-error (abs (- y-approx y-exact))
      'sum-error (abs (- sum-approx sum-exact))
      'error-bound (+ (abs (- x-approx x-exact)) 
                      (abs (- y-approx y-exact))))
```

[VISUAL: print the errors: `(x-error 0.0042... y-error 0.0020... sum-error 0.0063... error-bound 0.0063...)`. The sum's error is the sum of the errors.]

**Error propagation in multiplication:** If `x` and `y` have small relative errors `εₓ` and `εᵧ`, then `x · y` has relative error approximately `εₓ + εᵧ`.

<!-- BUILD: run through interpreter, demonstrate error propagation in a product -->

```scheme
(define x-approx 1.41)
(define x-exact (math/pow 2 0.5))
(define y-approx 1.73)
(define y-exact (math/pow 3 0.5))

(define prod-approx (* x-approx y-approx))
(define prod-exact (* x-exact y-exact))

(define rel-err-x (/ (abs (- x-approx x-exact)) x-exact))
(define rel-err-y (/ (abs (- y-approx y-exact)) y-exact))
(define rel-err-prod (/ (abs (- prod-approx prod-exact)) prod-exact))

(list 'rel-err-x rel-err-x
      'rel-err-y rel-err-y
      'rel-err-prod rel-err-prod
      'sum-of-rel-errs (+ rel-err-x rel-err-y))
```

[VISUAL: print the relative errors: `(rel-err-x 0.00296... rel-err-y 0.00115... rel-err-prod 0.00411... sum-of-rel-errs 0.00411...)`. The product's relative error ≈ sum of relative errors.]

